WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:09.965
[gentle acoustic guitar]

00:09.965 --> 00:11.965
[crickets chirping]

00:11.965 --> 00:19.000
♪

00:48.551 --> 00:55.620
♪

01:13.068 --> 01:16.206
- It's okay.
You remember me?

01:16.206 --> 01:17.620
Yeah.
It's all right.

01:17.620 --> 01:21.344
It's all right.

01:21.344 --> 01:24.103
That's it.
That's it.

01:24.103 --> 01:27.724
Good boy.
Good boy.

01:27.724 --> 01:34.758
♪

01:34.758 --> 01:36.793
[clicks tongue]

02:04.448 --> 02:06.586
[solemn orchestral music]

02:06.586 --> 02:14.482
♪

03:22.206 --> 03:23.655
Let's get you a drink.

03:23.655 --> 03:25.931
Whoa.

03:30.620 --> 03:31.862
[horse nickers]

03:31.862 --> 03:32.241
Hey.

03:34.896 --> 03:38.758
[bear grunting]

03:46.827 --> 03:48.275
Easy.
Easy, bear.

03:52.758 --> 03:56.689
[bear huffing]

03:59.517 --> 04:01.448
Easy, bear--hey.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

04:01.448 --> 04:03.103
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Whoa.

04:03.103 --> 04:05.206
Hey!
Whoa!

04:05.206 --> 04:07.551
Hey, bear!
Get out of here!

04:07.551 --> 04:09.965
Hey!

04:09.965 --> 04:11.827
Get out of here!

04:11.827 --> 04:12.517
Easy.

04:12.517 --> 04:15.689
[bear bellows, growls]

04:17.793 --> 04:19.724
Sorry, son.

04:19.724 --> 04:21.206
[screams]

04:21.206 --> 04:22.793
[gunshot]

04:38.413 --> 04:41.448
- You could get in trouble
in a church.

04:41.448 --> 04:43.724
You stood your ground,
though...

04:43.724 --> 04:44.931
for once.

04:44.931 --> 04:47.275
- I ain't used to seeing you
off my dad's leash.

04:49.448 --> 04:52.000
- What's that?
- I didn't stutter.

04:52.689 --> 04:55.275
- [groans]

04:58.137 --> 04:59.655
Go ahead. Come on.
Go ahead.

04:59.655 --> 05:01.896
[grunts]

05:01.896 --> 05:04.379
[both grunting]

05:11.517 --> 05:14.137
You still can't
take a punch, though.

05:14.137 --> 05:17.068
- Where the fuck you going?

05:17.068 --> 05:18.551
- Ah...

05:18.551 --> 05:21.275
there's work to be done.

05:21.275 --> 05:23.413
You know what work is,
don't you?

05:25.034 --> 05:26.620
Course you don't.

05:26.620 --> 05:29.000
You got your wife for that.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.482
By the way, welcome home.

05:35.965 --> 05:39.344
- [groans softly]

05:39.344 --> 05:41.310
- Only this wasn't a dream.

05:41.310 --> 05:42.344
It was the biggest fish
I ever caught.

05:44.793 --> 05:47.103
You're up early.

05:47.103 --> 05:49.551
- Tate has school.
So do I.

05:49.551 --> 05:51.482
Go on and brush your teeth.
We gotta go.

05:51.482 --> 05:53.482
- You drink coffee?

05:53.482 --> 05:56.482
- I'm a teacher.
We live on it.

05:56.482 --> 05:58.689
- There's breakfast up at
the house if you've got time.

05:58.689 --> 05:59.827
- We don't.

06:02.413 --> 06:05.482
- Well, I--
I brought this for Kayce.

06:05.482 --> 06:07.068
- Oh, he left early.
He's working on your horse.

06:07.068 --> 06:09.379
- Yeah, needs a lot of work.

06:09.379 --> 06:11.896
- Can someone give him
a ride back?

06:11.896 --> 06:14.448
I can't be late.
- We'll get him figured out.

06:14.448 --> 06:17.068
Thanks for staying
last night.

06:17.068 --> 06:17.586
It was good to have you here.

06:21.379 --> 06:23.068
- Why do they do it?

06:26.413 --> 06:28.965
The brand.
Why do the cowboys do that?

06:30.482 --> 06:33.206
- Well, they--
they don't all do it.

06:33.206 --> 06:37.068
Just the ones that
got a second chance.

06:37.068 --> 06:40.448
I guess that's the way they
prove they're to be trusted.

06:40.448 --> 06:43.103
- Is that why
you did it to Kayce?

06:43.103 --> 06:44.482
Couldn't trust him?

06:44.482 --> 06:45.551
[door clicks]

06:47.000 --> 06:48.034
- Hey.

06:48.034 --> 06:49.931
Why don't you, uh...

06:49.931 --> 06:53.172
Why don't you run to the house
and grab a big, fat donut

06:53.172 --> 06:53.896
so your growling stomach
don't drive your mom nuts

06:53.896 --> 06:55.310
on the way home?

06:55.310 --> 06:58.172
- Can I get the biggest donut?

06:58.172 --> 07:00.862
- Biggest one in there, buddy.
Go.

07:00.862 --> 07:03.000
[chuckles]

07:08.344 --> 07:10.965
I'm afraid that's
a longer conversation.

07:10.965 --> 07:12.172
- Well, if I'm gonna
be a part of this family,

07:12.172 --> 07:15.448
I need to understand it.

07:15.448 --> 07:18.517
I need to understand
why he hates you so much.

07:18.517 --> 07:20.655
- He disobeyed me
one too many times.

07:23.448 --> 07:24.655
- Disobeyed you how?

07:27.275 --> 07:30.206
- He told me he got some girl
he barely knew pregnant,

07:30.206 --> 07:32.793
and he was gonna marry her.

07:35.413 --> 07:37.448
- So it was because of me.

07:37.448 --> 07:40.689
- I told him to take you
to the clinic

07:40.689 --> 07:42.655
and not let you leave
until you had an abortion,

07:42.655 --> 07:44.448
and he wouldn't do it.

07:44.448 --> 07:46.482
[tense music]

07:46.482 --> 07:50.482
- So you had those cowboys
brand him?

07:52.310 --> 07:53.482
- No, Monica, that I...

07:56.103 --> 07:57.931
That I did myself.

07:57.931 --> 08:04.689
♪

08:04.689 --> 08:05.620
- Okay. I understand now.

08:08.310 --> 08:11.068
Thank you for your honesty.

08:11.068 --> 08:18.206
♪

08:27.793 --> 08:30.137
[footsteps thudding]

08:32.102 --> 08:33.895
- Pick one yet?

08:33.895 --> 08:35.827
- Hard to tell
which one's the biggest.

08:35.827 --> 08:37.620
- Yeah, I know.
They're all pretty fat.

08:40.448 --> 08:41.827
[sighs]

08:41.827 --> 08:45.793
How about we
line them up in a row,

08:45.793 --> 08:49.103
and then the biggest
will be easier to spot then.

08:49.103 --> 08:52.551
- You can do that?

08:52.551 --> 08:53.793
- [chuckling]
Yeah.

08:53.793 --> 08:55.827
Grandson, you can--

08:55.827 --> 08:59.551
you can do whatever you want.

08:59.551 --> 09:03.241
[soft dramatic music]

09:03.241 --> 09:05.000
[grunts softly]

09:05.000 --> 09:07.586
[chuckles]

09:07.586 --> 09:14.655
♪

09:43.758 --> 09:46.103
- Came here to escape work,
babe.

09:46.103 --> 09:47.206
- Oh, not working.

09:47.206 --> 09:50.689
This is fascinating.

09:50.689 --> 09:52.310
Did you know
the livestock association

09:52.310 --> 09:54.206
has its own police force?

09:54.206 --> 09:56.931
- Oh.
- Huh.

09:58.655 --> 10:01.758
Hey, remember that thing
on CNN about the--

10:01.758 --> 10:05.931
the shootout over cattle
on an Indian reservation?

10:05.931 --> 10:07.586
Look at this.

10:07.586 --> 10:09.448
This is the guy.

10:09.448 --> 10:11.448
- That's great, babe.

10:11.448 --> 10:14.551
- I feel like I'm reading about
crooked cops in fucking Queens.

10:14.551 --> 10:17.310
This is the same thing.
- Now you're working.

10:17.310 --> 10:19.586
- Yeah, damn right I am.

10:23.517 --> 10:26.517
- There's a beautiful property
just south of the Yellowstone.

10:26.517 --> 10:28.827
230 acres, Live Water.

10:28.827 --> 10:30.344
- Does it border
the Yellowstone?

10:30.344 --> 10:31.931
- It's about
a mile down the road.

10:31.931 --> 10:33.724
- Oh, it's gotta border
the Yellowstone.

10:33.724 --> 10:34.965
Do you see all these
lots for sale?

10:34.965 --> 10:35.896
- Yep.

10:35.896 --> 10:38.241
What is "Paradise Valley
Development"?

10:38.241 --> 10:40.965
- That's Dan Jenkins'
planned living community.

10:40.965 --> 10:42.965
It's not what
you're looking for.

10:42.965 --> 10:44.551
20, 30 acre lots,

10:44.551 --> 10:46.103
but there's no power
on that side of the valley.

10:46.103 --> 10:48.482
And its zoned commercial,
so there's no telling what--

10:48.482 --> 10:51.000
- Could you print me out
a plat map?

10:59.965 --> 11:02.896
Thank you.

11:06.413 --> 11:07.724
This is what I need.

11:07.724 --> 11:10.620
- All of those lots will
be bank-owned within a year.

11:10.620 --> 11:12.551
Dan Jenkins
lost the water source

11:12.551 --> 11:15.551
he was using to generate power.

11:15.551 --> 11:17.000
- How do you lose water?

11:17.000 --> 11:20.379
- John Dutton
rerouted the river.

11:20.379 --> 11:22.896
- He rerouted the river?
- Yeah.

11:24.482 --> 11:28.206
It will cost between
15 to 25 million

11:28.206 --> 11:29.896
to get power down there.

11:29.896 --> 11:30.827
You don't want
one of those lots.

11:30.827 --> 11:33.310
Trust me.
They're worthless.

11:33.310 --> 11:35.517
- I don't want one of them.

11:35.517 --> 11:36.758
I want all of them.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.620
- If you come on my leather
seats, you're walking home.

11:58.689 --> 11:59.965
- We're already late.

11:59.965 --> 12:03.793
- The meeting can't start
without us, Jamie.

12:05.724 --> 12:07.724
- [sighs softly]

12:22.068 --> 12:24.655
- I need to go to the bathroom.

12:33.103 --> 12:34.793
- [sighs]

12:42.586 --> 12:44.172
After you.

12:46.137 --> 12:49.551
- We've been waiting
a long time for this, Jamie.

12:49.551 --> 12:52.000
And you--what a surprise.

12:52.000 --> 12:54.103
I had no idea you were
interested in politics.

12:54.103 --> 12:54.724
- I'm not.

12:54.724 --> 12:56.379
But what daddy wants,

12:56.379 --> 12:58.000
daddy gets, right?

12:59.206 --> 13:00.172
- Our plan is this.

13:00.172 --> 13:02.620
Mike announces
his decision not to run.

13:02.620 --> 13:03.965
At the same time,
he endorses you

13:03.965 --> 13:05.862
as his choice to succeed him.

13:05.862 --> 13:09.034
Christina interned
for Chris Messina in 2012.

13:09.034 --> 13:11.655
- Obama's campaign manager.

13:11.655 --> 13:14.034
- I know who he is.
- Of course you do.

13:14.034 --> 13:16.172
- She's been staffed with us
for three years

13:16.172 --> 13:19.310
and was instrumental
in our gain of five seats

13:19.310 --> 13:20.931
in the Assembly in 2016.

13:20.931 --> 13:24.862
We think she'd be a great asset
to your campaign.

13:24.862 --> 13:26.344
- I'm really excited
to get started.

13:26.344 --> 13:29.172
- Well, I'm happy
to have you on the team.

13:29.172 --> 13:30.862
- [laughs]

13:33.965 --> 13:37.586
Can my whore be a 6-foot
fireman who loves Jesus?

13:37.586 --> 13:38.896
Please?
[laughs softly]

13:40.724 --> 13:41.931
- The Dutton name
gives you the red votes.

13:41.931 --> 13:44.827
Mike's endorsement
gives you the blue votes.

13:44.827 --> 13:48.758
- So you want me to run
as an independent?

13:48.758 --> 13:51.517
That opens me up to opposition
from both parties.

13:51.517 --> 13:55.206
And it limits the possibilities
for an office beyond this one.

13:55.206 --> 13:58.689
- Let's just worry about
winning this office for now.

13:58.689 --> 13:59.620
There's a value
to the independent party

13:59.620 --> 14:02.275
that didn't exist
ten years ago.

14:02.275 --> 14:04.000
- The partisan lines
are drawn so deep.

14:04.000 --> 14:05.931
The only way to get
anything accomplished

14:05.931 --> 14:08.965
is with a swing vote;
party members don't get those.

14:08.965 --> 14:11.103
- It's the new trend because
it benefits both parties.

14:11.103 --> 14:12.931
- If you run independent,
you'll run unopposed.

14:12.931 --> 14:16.241
- Both party chairs
have pledged that.

14:16.241 --> 14:17.827
- So, if he's
running unopposed,

14:17.827 --> 14:20.241
why does he need this
little firecracker?

14:20.241 --> 14:23.413
Or do these kind of perks
come with the office?

14:24.689 --> 14:27.172
- Can I have a word
with Beth alone?

14:35.000 --> 14:36.517
- Don't you fuck this up
for me.

14:36.517 --> 14:39.310
- I'm fucking it up
just for me.

14:44.241 --> 14:45.068
[door clicks]

14:47.068 --> 14:47.896
- I get the sense
there's something

14:47.896 --> 14:50.000
that you would like to discuss.

14:50.000 --> 14:52.931
- What insight.
No wonder you're governor.

14:55.758 --> 14:57.655
- When my husband died,

14:57.655 --> 15:00.586
our son was 15.

15:00.586 --> 15:02.827
He's had countless
issues since--

15:02.827 --> 15:05.206
drug abuse, alcohol abuse,

15:05.206 --> 15:07.448
pretty significant
gambling addiction.

15:07.448 --> 15:09.517
He can't hold down a job.

15:09.517 --> 15:12.517
Although, I hear that you're
a highly-functioning alcoholic,

15:12.517 --> 15:14.689
so kudos for that.

15:14.689 --> 15:17.482
What I learned, painfully,

15:17.482 --> 15:20.344
is that when a child
suffers a tragedy,

15:20.344 --> 15:21.724
they stop maturing.

15:21.724 --> 15:23.137
They're emotionally frozen

15:23.137 --> 15:25.620
at the age
they experienced the loss...

15:25.620 --> 15:29.103
until they accept it,

15:29.103 --> 15:30.965
which, clearly, you haven't.

15:30.965 --> 15:35.275
I look at you, and I see
a 14-year-old girl

15:35.275 --> 15:38.517
who wants to bully the world.

15:38.517 --> 15:41.827
But you can't bully me, Beth.

15:41.827 --> 15:45.137
Bullies need to be big,

15:45.137 --> 15:47.586
and I'm bigger than you.

15:49.620 --> 15:50.862
Got it?

15:52.413 --> 15:54.172
- Boy, do I.

15:54.172 --> 15:58.689
- I can't endorse you for
office until you get some help.

15:58.689 --> 16:00.172
- You're endorsing my brother,

16:00.172 --> 16:02.551
which shows your
shrewd judge of character.

16:02.551 --> 16:05.034
I don't want your endorsement.
That's not why I'm here.

16:05.586 --> 16:09.034
- Okay, Beth.

16:09.034 --> 16:11.344
[tense music]

16:11.344 --> 16:14.310
♪

16:14.310 --> 16:16.896
Fire away.

16:16.896 --> 16:19.137
- Men don't think like us.

16:19.137 --> 16:22.724
Too simple to weigh
the significance of every act.

16:22.724 --> 16:26.827
My father,
he just wants to forget.

16:26.827 --> 16:29.103
But not you.

16:29.103 --> 16:31.241
You wanna piss in every corner

16:31.241 --> 16:35.034
and make those corners yours.

16:35.034 --> 16:37.551
Affairs happen in hotels,

16:37.551 --> 16:39.000
not homes.

16:41.517 --> 16:44.344
You need to look closer
when you look at me,

16:44.344 --> 16:46.896
Lynelle.

16:46.896 --> 16:49.448
I ruin careers for a living.

16:49.448 --> 16:52.862
[shuffling]

16:52.862 --> 16:55.586
You sleep in
my mother's bed again,

16:55.586 --> 16:58.344
and I will ruin yours.

16:58.344 --> 17:01.413
Ruin it.

17:01.413 --> 17:03.827
Got it?

17:03.827 --> 17:06.862
And tell your son to grow up.

17:06.862 --> 17:10.792
He sounds like a real pussy.

17:10.792 --> 17:12.413
- I love Old Man Lee's.
- No way.

17:12.413 --> 17:13.344
- No. Beth--

17:13.344 --> 17:14.862
- Ready.

17:14.862 --> 17:18.205
- Hey, we're not
going anywhere.

17:18.205 --> 17:20.964
We're just getting started.
- Hey, I can give you a ride.

17:20.964 --> 17:22.619
- Ah, I'll figure it out.

17:22.619 --> 17:25.034
Well, the ranch is far.

17:25.034 --> 17:25.964
- I work for you now.

17:25.964 --> 17:27.964
I'll take you
anywhere you want.

17:27.964 --> 17:29.655
- Jamie?

17:33.793 --> 17:35.068
Just Jamie.

17:35.068 --> 17:39.275
- I'll be in my office,
then court.

17:39.275 --> 17:41.517
- I'll be right outside
the door if you need me.

17:41.517 --> 17:44.068
[door clicks]

17:44.068 --> 17:45.655
- Looks like
that's gonna work out.

17:45.655 --> 17:47.655
- Yeah, she seems great.

17:47.655 --> 17:49.103
- [laughs softly]

17:49.103 --> 17:51.896
Well, I'm hoping it
really works out, Jamie.

17:51.896 --> 17:54.103
A 36-year-old bachelor
running for office

17:54.103 --> 17:55.862
raises a lot of questions.

17:55.862 --> 17:57.068
- You want us to pretend
to be a couple?

17:57.068 --> 17:58.827
[chuckles]
- No.

17:58.827 --> 18:00.586
It looks like it's
happening organically.

18:00.586 --> 18:02.000
That's a good thing.

18:02.000 --> 18:04.137
Let's talk about
something else.

18:04.137 --> 18:06.206
Some members of the
Livestock Association

18:06.206 --> 18:07.965
have raised some health
concerns regarding your father.

18:07.965 --> 18:10.413
- Health concerns?
Like--like what?

18:10.413 --> 18:12.344
- Like cancer.

18:12.344 --> 18:15.586
- [laughing]
That's--that's, uh--

18:15.586 --> 18:17.172
I think I would know.

18:18.413 --> 18:19.931
- Would you?

18:19.931 --> 18:21.206
- I wouldn't listen
to the rumor mill

18:21.206 --> 18:22.793
at the Cattleman's Association.

18:22.793 --> 18:25.275
- Well, I don't pay much
attention to that, except

18:25.275 --> 18:28.655
when one of the association
member's sons is a Oncologist.

18:32.793 --> 18:34.586
Now, I would like to think--

18:42.206 --> 18:44.068
- Wait, do you need a ride?

18:44.068 --> 18:46.241
- Um, no, thanks.
[stammers] Sorry.

18:58.965 --> 19:01.724
- Wanna go again?

19:01.724 --> 19:03.103
Let's go.
- No, no, no.

19:03.103 --> 19:06.275
I think we got it
out of our system...

19:06.275 --> 19:07.758
for now.

19:07.758 --> 19:10.655
[horse snorts]

19:12.896 --> 19:16.172
My job is to protect
this family,

19:16.172 --> 19:20.275
and you are the
worst thing for it.

19:20.275 --> 19:22.896
You made your choice, Kayce.

19:22.896 --> 19:25.482
Now you stand by it.

19:25.482 --> 19:28.344
Don't come back now.

19:28.344 --> 19:30.551
You wanna do something
for your father?

19:30.551 --> 19:34.034
You do that,

19:34.034 --> 19:36.931
'cause I'll be honest with you.

19:36.931 --> 19:39.896
I'm getting tired
of burying your secrets.

19:39.896 --> 19:42.137
[horse snorts]
Come on, come on.

19:42.137 --> 19:44.137
[clicks tongue]
Come on.

19:44.137 --> 19:47.275
[soft dramatic music]

19:47.275 --> 19:54.137
♪

20:02.000 --> 20:04.034
- What are you thinking?

20:05.896 --> 20:07.310
- [sighs]
[pen clatters]

20:07.310 --> 20:09.862
I'm thinking
she can't be controlled.

20:09.862 --> 20:13.137
- I could've told you that.

20:13.137 --> 20:15.137
Second thoughts on Jamie too?

20:15.137 --> 20:17.379
- Well, Jamie's a politician
and a realist.

20:17.379 --> 20:19.137
That's not the office
I'm thinking about.

20:21.586 --> 20:24.689
John's making bad decisions.

20:24.689 --> 20:27.172
The way he handled
the BLM issue was reckless.

20:27.172 --> 20:28.896
The way he covered it up
was more reckless.

20:28.896 --> 20:32.068
Asking me to consider
his daughter

20:32.068 --> 20:34.793
for any public office?

20:34.793 --> 20:39.137
[scoffs]
He's just not adapting.

20:39.137 --> 20:39.896
If anything, he's regressing.

20:39.896 --> 20:42.310
He's acting like it's 1985,

20:42.310 --> 20:43.724
and no one's
looking over our shoulder.

20:43.724 --> 20:47.241
- Supporting another candidate
for Livestock Commissioner

20:47.241 --> 20:49.793
is the nuclear option, Lynelle.

20:49.793 --> 20:53.000
You obviously lose the
crossover votes he provides.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.172
You make an enemy
out of your new AG.

20:55.172 --> 20:56.206
- No, you'd have
to stick around.

20:56.206 --> 20:58.517
- Don't put me
in that position.

20:58.517 --> 21:01.551
- All right, let's just not
jump to any conclusions.

21:03.413 --> 21:06.344
But if we backed someone else,

21:06.344 --> 21:08.965
who would that someone be?

21:08.965 --> 21:11.793
- Let's think about that.

21:15.310 --> 21:16.862
- Why can't we just
live with grandpa?

21:16.862 --> 21:20.379
- Because our home is here.

21:20.379 --> 21:21.758
- I like his home better.

21:21.758 --> 21:26.103
Our home sucks balls.

21:26.103 --> 21:29.724
- Tate, where do you learn
that kind of language?

21:29.724 --> 21:30.965
- School.

21:30.965 --> 21:32.758
Probably better
I shouldn't go there

21:32.758 --> 21:34.413
from all the bad things
I learn.

21:34.413 --> 21:35.724
- Mm-hmm.

21:35.724 --> 21:38.448
- Wonder what cuss word
I'm gonna learn today.

21:40.241 --> 21:42.586
- Nice try, kid.

21:44.862 --> 21:48.724
[kids shouting indistinctly]

21:55.068 --> 21:57.137
[kids chanting]
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

22:03.758 --> 22:05.482
- Come here.

22:05.482 --> 22:07.689
Hold my hand.
Let's go.

22:07.689 --> 22:10.827
[chanting continues]

22:10.827 --> 22:13.827
[kids shouting]

22:13.827 --> 22:15.689
Hey, look at me.

22:15.689 --> 22:18.448
Stay right here, okay?

22:19.758 --> 22:22.482
Hey!

22:22.482 --> 22:25.379
Hey!
Hey!

22:25.379 --> 22:27.758
Stop it!

22:27.758 --> 22:28.689
Stop it--
[blow lands]

22:28.689 --> 22:31.275
[kids gasping]

22:31.275 --> 22:32.827
- Oh, my God.

22:32.827 --> 22:35.448
[tense music]

22:35.448 --> 22:37.965
- Mama!

22:37.965 --> 22:42.517
♪

22:42.517 --> 22:45.655
Mama!

22:45.655 --> 22:47.827
[screams]

22:47.827 --> 22:52.379
♪

22:52.379 --> 22:55.206
Mama!

22:58.586 --> 22:59.758
[phone vibrating]

22:59.758 --> 23:01.931
[door clicks]

23:09.482 --> 23:10.758
- Hello?

23:11.862 --> 23:13.862
This is him.

23:16.689 --> 23:20.206
Wha--where is she?

23:20.206 --> 23:22.965
N-No, I'll be--
I'll be right there.

23:22.965 --> 23:25.931
[dramatic music]

23:25.931 --> 23:29.068
♪

23:29.068 --> 23:30.206
- Wanna talk about the bruise?

23:34.655 --> 23:37.310
- Fell off the horse.
- Yeah.

23:37.310 --> 23:39.379
That a fact?

23:39.379 --> 23:42.034
Son, there's--
- I don't wanna hear it.

23:42.034 --> 23:43.206
- I'm not trying--

23:43.206 --> 23:44.689
- I don't wanna hear it.

23:46.448 --> 23:49.827
- Well, God damn it,
maybe you need to hear it, son,

23:49.827 --> 23:53.724
because every day,
it's something new with you.

23:53.724 --> 23:56.896
- It could've happened
at any school, anywhere.

23:56.896 --> 23:59.034
- But it didn't, did it?

23:59.034 --> 24:01.689
It happened at hers.

24:01.689 --> 24:04.000
♪

24:04.000 --> 24:07.275
- I don't wanna talk about it.

24:07.275 --> 24:13.655
♪

24:15.724 --> 24:17.862
Anywhere's fine.
Just let me out here.

24:17.862 --> 24:19.275
- Well, there's a spot--

24:19.275 --> 24:20.965
- Stop the fucking truck!

24:20.965 --> 24:22.827
[brakes squeal]

24:22.827 --> 24:30.689
♪

24:41.344 --> 24:43.379
Are you okay?

24:43.379 --> 24:46.413
- Well, I got a pretty
good headache going.

24:46.413 --> 24:48.724
- Any dizziness, nausea,

24:48.724 --> 24:49.758
saying things that
don't make sense--

24:49.758 --> 24:53.275
straight to the hospital.
- Yes, ma'am.

25:08.655 --> 25:10.724
- Oh.

25:10.724 --> 25:12.034
Can I have one day
without a crisis, God?

25:12.034 --> 25:15.793
Please, just one fucking day.

25:15.793 --> 25:16.310
[gear stick thunks]

25:21.655 --> 25:23.862
How bad?

25:23.862 --> 25:25.931
- You tell me.

25:31.379 --> 25:32.620
[phone beeps]

25:35.379 --> 25:38.241
- What's up, bud?
- How busy are you, Carl?

25:38.241 --> 25:38.758
- Well, compared to what?

25:38.758 --> 25:41.862
[knocking]

25:41.862 --> 25:43.758
- Just hold on.

25:46.620 --> 25:50.034
Can I just have one
fucking minute to myself here?

25:50.034 --> 25:50.379
Please?

25:53.689 --> 25:56.379
I need a break.

25:56.379 --> 25:58.275
- I'll be off by 5:00.

25:58.275 --> 25:59.689
- All right,
I'll meet you then.

25:59.689 --> 26:00.689
[phone beeps]

26:00.689 --> 26:02.724
[grumbles]
[phone clatters]

26:07.103 --> 26:09.965
[sighs]

26:09.965 --> 26:11.413
What?

26:11.413 --> 26:12.482
- [stammers]
- No, not yet.

26:12.482 --> 26:15.241
You and I are gonna
have a conversation.

26:15.241 --> 26:16.965
What?

26:16.965 --> 26:19.413
- Talk to me about cancer.

26:19.413 --> 26:21.620
- Okay.
What would you like to know?

26:21.620 --> 26:24.172
- For a start,
how long have you had it?

26:24.172 --> 26:26.551
- Well, I don't have a cancer.

26:26.551 --> 26:28.379
I had a tumor in my colon.
It was removed.

26:30.344 --> 26:30.965
[chuckles]

26:30.965 --> 26:32.620
Nice, uh...

26:32.620 --> 26:34.896
Nice to see you two exhibit
some real emotion.

26:34.896 --> 26:37.586
- This isn't funny.

26:37.586 --> 26:40.068
These aren't the kind of
secrets that you can keep.

26:40.068 --> 26:42.275
- Yeah, well, it doesn't
seem like much of a secret.

26:42.275 --> 26:44.896
- That could be
its own problem.

26:44.896 --> 26:47.310
- Well, lucky I have you
to take care of it.

26:50.000 --> 26:51.551
You come with me.

26:51.551 --> 26:53.586
[footsteps clacking]
[door clicks]

27:00.000 --> 27:01.103
[door slams]

27:05.068 --> 27:06.689
[clattering]

27:09.172 --> 27:10.413
You embarrassed me, Beth.

27:12.689 --> 27:14.310
- She's not
who you think she is.

27:14.310 --> 27:15.793
- She's exactly
who I think she is.

27:15.793 --> 27:17.172
She's just not
who you think she is.

27:17.172 --> 27:21.655
- [sighs]
- She's my friend.

27:21.655 --> 27:23.379
Your friend, too,
if you bothered to notice.

27:23.379 --> 27:25.965
- It's not casual to her.

27:25.965 --> 27:27.482
- Well, I don't know
what to tell you, Beth.

27:27.482 --> 27:28.241
If the governor's
not good enough for you,

27:28.241 --> 27:30.517
please explain your standards.

27:30.517 --> 27:32.517
- My standard is my mother.

27:32.517 --> 27:34.793
[glass clattering]

27:36.344 --> 27:38.275
- Now, you're
the only child I have

27:38.275 --> 27:40.758
tough enough
to take this advice.

27:40.758 --> 27:42.620
Now, you need to man up,
you understand?

27:42.620 --> 27:45.517
You need to man up,
be a part of the solution,

27:45.517 --> 27:47.517
or go back to fucking Utah!

27:49.862 --> 27:51.448
And don't you ever

27:51.448 --> 27:54.620
mention your mother
to me again.

27:54.620 --> 27:57.448
You forfeited that right
a long time ago.

28:05.655 --> 28:08.724
- [shaky breathing]

28:09.413 --> 28:12.862
[lounge music playing]

28:12.862 --> 28:19.965
♪

28:21.793 --> 28:24.931
- I gotta say, Dan,
you did real good here.

28:24.931 --> 28:27.724
Never thought it would
turn out like this.

28:27.724 --> 28:30.103
- A community by the park
would've been better.

28:30.103 --> 28:32.413
You see, people don't need
to drive to work anymore.

28:32.413 --> 28:34.103
Work is where you
open your laptop.

28:34.103 --> 28:37.103
That means people
get to live where they want.

28:37.103 --> 28:39.241
It's the first time in history
that option's become available

28:39.241 --> 28:41.793
to anyone
but the world's elite.

28:41.793 --> 28:44.310
- I'm not the bank, Dan.
You don't have to sell me.

28:44.310 --> 28:47.551
Let's talk about this problem.

28:47.551 --> 28:49.482
Getting a little pushback
from the good old boys, huh?

28:49.482 --> 28:51.344
- No, no, no.
He's more than that.

28:51.344 --> 28:52.724
He has influence over almost

28:52.724 --> 28:55.586
every public office
in the state.

28:55.586 --> 28:57.896
Now, nothing happens in this
county without his approval.

28:57.896 --> 28:59.793
- Tell me who he doesn't
have influence over.

28:59.793 --> 29:01.482
- A freshman senator...
- Mm-hmm.

29:01.482 --> 29:04.000
- A county attorney
from Livingston,

29:04.000 --> 29:05.931
and half the democrats
in Bozeman.

29:05.931 --> 29:07.068
- That's a start.
[glass clacks]

29:07.068 --> 29:09.103
What about this
Livestock Association?

29:09.103 --> 29:11.206
Any young, ambitious rancher
looking to move up?

29:11.206 --> 29:13.413
- Not around here, no.

29:13.413 --> 29:15.000
- Well, we don't look here.

29:15.000 --> 29:16.000
We go to Missoula.

29:16.000 --> 29:19.896
We go to Miles City
or Great Falls...

29:19.896 --> 29:23.724
somewhere that doesn't know
Bozeman and doesn't care.

29:23.724 --> 29:25.655
I'll start to look.

29:25.655 --> 29:27.137
You don't beat this guy
in a stand-up fight.

29:27.137 --> 29:31.241
You gotta kill him

29:31.241 --> 29:34.620
with a thousand little cuts.

29:34.620 --> 29:36.793
I'll reach out to environmental
organizations.

29:36.793 --> 29:38.862
This close to the park,
there's bound to be

29:38.862 --> 29:41.241
threatened species
on his property.

29:41.241 --> 29:42.862
Was that river he moved

29:42.862 --> 29:45.896
a spawning ground for
the Yellowstone cutthroat,

29:45.896 --> 29:49.103
or can we sue to place
trail cameras on his property

29:49.103 --> 29:51.689
to monitor migrating
wolverines, pine martens...

29:51.689 --> 29:53.620
- [chuckling]
- Both endangered in this area.

29:53.620 --> 29:56.931
What?
- I forgot how good you are.

29:56.931 --> 29:59.241
- Baby, when you pay
the Armageddon rate,

29:59.241 --> 30:02.103
God sends you an angel.

30:02.103 --> 30:04.655
What we need to find
is the face of this fight.

30:04.655 --> 30:07.310
Can't be you.
- Well, who else could it be?

30:07.310 --> 30:08.517
I'm not bringing in
any partners.

30:08.517 --> 30:10.275
- Not partners, but...

30:10.275 --> 30:12.862
understand you could find
the cure for Alzheimer's.

30:12.862 --> 30:15.275
These people would
still hate you.

30:15.275 --> 30:16.620
You're a billionaire
from California.

30:16.620 --> 30:18.827
- Half of Bozeman is
billionaires from California.

30:18.827 --> 30:20.724
- They're all wishing
they weren't.

30:20.724 --> 30:23.758
Deep down, y'all wish
you were cowboys.

30:23.758 --> 30:26.620
It's the white version of
a brother from Beverly Hills

30:26.620 --> 30:28.206
pretending he's hard.

30:28.206 --> 30:29.448
[laughs]
No.

30:29.448 --> 30:31.137
We need to find a face.

30:31.137 --> 30:34.448
It isn't yours.

30:34.448 --> 30:37.206
- Use my face.

30:37.206 --> 30:38.793
I, for the past month,

30:38.793 --> 30:40.689
have been doing what
you're doing right now,

30:40.689 --> 30:43.586
and I came to
the same conclusion:

30:43.586 --> 30:46.206
I can't beat them alone.

30:46.206 --> 30:47.862
Tom Rainwater,

30:47.862 --> 30:50.758
Chairman of the confederated
tribe at Broken Rock.

30:50.758 --> 30:53.413
- Aren't you gonna
introduce yourself to me?

30:53.413 --> 30:54.827
- What for?

30:54.827 --> 30:56.275
You aren't the one
calling the shots.

30:56.275 --> 30:58.275
- I like the way you think.

30:58.275 --> 30:59.137
She calls the shots,
I approve them,

30:59.137 --> 31:01.586
'cause I write the checks.

31:01.586 --> 31:03.413
- Not anymore.

31:03.413 --> 31:04.896
I'll do that too.

31:06.862 --> 31:09.413
- Walk me through your ideas.
- No, no, no, Melody.

31:09.413 --> 31:11.137
This doesn't sound
like strategy.

31:11.137 --> 31:13.724
This sounds like business--
business he walks me through.

31:16.206 --> 31:18.482
- You have a subdivision
that you can't build

31:18.482 --> 31:20.689
because you have
no power source.

31:20.689 --> 31:21.620
I can give that to you.

31:21.620 --> 31:24.448
- That's a $60 million build.

31:24.448 --> 31:26.137
- I'll get a loan.

31:26.137 --> 31:28.482
- You'll get a loan to
help build a subdivision?

31:28.482 --> 31:31.413
- The loan is not
for a subdivision.

31:31.413 --> 31:33.103
It's for a casino.

31:37.551 --> 31:39.896
- I'll lease you
the land for a dollar.

31:39.896 --> 31:41.827
- Won't give me the loan
for a lease.

31:41.827 --> 31:43.241
We have to own the land.

31:44.620 --> 31:46.379
- How much land do you need?
- Dan.

31:46.379 --> 31:48.793
- 40 acres for the casino.

31:48.793 --> 31:51.448
I'd like 75 for a hotel
and parking.

31:51.448 --> 31:53.206
- Dan.

31:53.206 --> 31:56.827
- You can choose a location.
You can have design approval.

31:56.827 --> 31:58.827
I do have minimum
square foot requirements

31:58.827 --> 32:00.724
for the casino and parking,

32:00.724 --> 32:03.034
and I have minimum room
requirements for the hotel.

32:03.034 --> 32:06.137
But I finance all construction.

32:06.137 --> 32:09.448
I will build your roads,
in and out.

32:09.448 --> 32:11.896
Water, power, sewage--

32:11.896 --> 32:14.482
I finance all infrastructure

32:14.482 --> 32:16.758
and then lease
your subdivision access

32:16.758 --> 32:20.379
to the infrastructure
for 1% of the casino revenue.

32:20.379 --> 32:23.000
- Why would I agree to that?
- [laughs softly]

32:23.000 --> 32:25.448
Because I'm giving you
15% revenue

32:25.448 --> 32:27.137
as payment for the land.

32:29.551 --> 32:31.551
- Well, how big is the casino?

32:31.551 --> 32:35.620
- 275,000 square feet
on the casino floor,

32:35.620 --> 32:38.482
400 rooms in the hotel.

32:38.482 --> 32:40.482
- That's a $200 million
build, huh?

32:40.482 --> 32:43.241
- 300.
- Dan.

32:43.241 --> 32:43.793
A word?

32:46.413 --> 32:48.137
- Excuse me.

32:51.034 --> 32:55.034
- Don't agree to anything.
I need to do some digging.

32:55.034 --> 32:56.551
- Well, dig away, but that's
the deal of the century.

32:56.551 --> 32:58.862
- It's too good to be true.

32:58.862 --> 33:01.000
- Well, he's
too desperate to lie.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.827
When you dig him up,
you'll understand.

33:02.827 --> 33:05.172
That's the enemy of my enemy,

33:05.172 --> 33:06.379
and John Dutton
has no greater enemy

33:06.379 --> 33:09.379
than that man right there.

33:09.379 --> 33:12.413
[soft dramatic music]

33:12.413 --> 33:14.344
Tom.

33:15.379 --> 33:17.413
- Great.

33:17.413 --> 33:21.275
♪

33:21.275 --> 33:22.689
- Well...

33:22.689 --> 33:26.620
would your friend
care to join us?

33:26.620 --> 33:28.344
- Well, he's a little
occupied right now.

33:28.344 --> 33:29.379
[both chuckling]
- Exactly.

33:33.655 --> 33:35.586
- I wanna put it in.

33:35.586 --> 33:37.620
- I'll let you put it in.

33:37.620 --> 33:39.931
- Then why are you holding it?
- There you go.

33:39.931 --> 33:41.689
Take these.
- I'm giving it to you.

33:41.689 --> 33:44.241
- Then give it to me.

33:44.241 --> 33:47.275
- Do I have your permission
to teach this boy some manners?

33:47.275 --> 33:48.689
both: Yes.

33:51.689 --> 33:54.344
- You lied!
- Come with me.

33:57.620 --> 34:01.655
Your mother will not
punish you

34:01.655 --> 34:05.413
because she is your mother.

34:05.413 --> 34:09.103
Your father's whole childhood

34:09.103 --> 34:10.688
was punishment.

34:10.688 --> 34:12.413
Because of that,
he does not trust himself

34:12.413 --> 34:15.585
to do it in a good way,

34:15.585 --> 34:18.551
so he doesn't do it at all.

34:18.551 --> 34:21.310
That brings us to you.

34:21.310 --> 34:24.896
You need to be a good kid

34:24.896 --> 34:27.896
because you want to be
a good kid.

34:27.896 --> 34:31.827
Because your parents
do not have the heart

34:31.827 --> 34:33.931
to make you into a good kid.

34:33.931 --> 34:38.379
I did not have the heart
with my grandson...

34:40.793 --> 34:43.275
And now he's gone.

34:45.206 --> 34:46.757
Does that make sense?

34:49.655 --> 34:52.344
Didn't figure it would.

34:52.344 --> 34:54.688
It was worth a shot, though.

34:54.688 --> 34:57.655
- Do you think
the pasta's ready?

34:57.655 --> 34:59.689
- A few more minutes.

35:02.724 --> 35:05.206
Let's go back inside.

35:08.655 --> 35:09.275
- Look,

35:09.275 --> 35:12.862
a spaceship.

35:12.862 --> 35:14.896
- You feeling any better?

35:14.896 --> 35:16.310
- Well, the kid
can throw a punch.

35:16.310 --> 35:17.724
I'll say that.

35:17.724 --> 35:19.793
- How many fingers
am I holding up?

35:20.206 --> 35:22.034
- 17.

35:24.413 --> 35:26.586
Hey, do you think
we're doing the right thing?

35:26.586 --> 35:28.344
Tate has the opportunity
to live like

35:28.344 --> 35:32.482
99% of the country
will never understand.

35:32.482 --> 35:35.000
- I understand it.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.241
Look how I turned out.

35:37.241 --> 35:40.379
[horse neighs]

35:41.413 --> 35:45.241
[horse whinnying]

35:46.448 --> 35:49.689
I'll be right back.

35:49.689 --> 35:51.172
Hey, don't fall asleep.

35:51.172 --> 35:53.379
- Okay.

35:53.379 --> 35:55.827
[footsteps fading]

35:59.620 --> 36:02.620
[horse neighing]

36:02.620 --> 36:04.862
[drone buzzing]

36:09.413 --> 36:12.310
- What the hell
is that thing doing?

36:12.310 --> 36:16.275
- No clue.

36:16.275 --> 36:18.620
- Get inside.

36:18.620 --> 36:20.310
- Is it from space?

36:21.344 --> 36:23.551
- It's a drone, son.
- What's a drone?

36:23.551 --> 36:25.000
- Know a guy on the Flathead

36:25.000 --> 36:28.206
said treasure hunters
fly them all over,

36:28.206 --> 36:30.517
looking for a place to dig.

36:31.793 --> 36:34.620
- It ain't gonna find
no treasure around here.

36:34.620 --> 36:37.241
- My dinosaur!

36:37.241 --> 36:38.620
- Tate, stop.

36:38.620 --> 36:41.275
Tate!
Tate, stop.

36:41.275 --> 36:43.620
Stay behind me.
[horse nickers]

36:43.620 --> 36:45.896
[buzzing continues]

36:54.793 --> 36:56.620
[gunshot]

36:56.620 --> 36:58.000
[drone clatters]

37:03.517 --> 37:05.448
[soft dramatic music]

37:05.448 --> 37:11.103
♪

37:11.103 --> 37:15.896
- White people just
fucking take, take, take.

37:15.896 --> 37:18.413
I don't mean you.
- I know what you mean.

37:18.413 --> 37:25.482
♪

37:30.413 --> 37:32.586
- Cut him off!

37:32.586 --> 37:37.896
♪

37:42.206 --> 37:45.137
- Leave the shotgun here.

37:45.137 --> 37:45.965
Hey.
[car door slams]

37:45.965 --> 37:47.724
Hey!
Stop the car.

37:47.724 --> 37:49.896
[banging]
Stop the car!

37:49.896 --> 37:51.344
I just wanna talk!
Stop--

37:51.344 --> 37:54.379
[car revving]
[tires squealing]

37:56.655 --> 38:00.413
[gunshot]

38:00.413 --> 38:02.793
- I had him!

38:02.793 --> 38:04.896
I was aiming for the tire.

38:04.896 --> 38:06.517
- Yeah?

38:06.517 --> 38:07.689
And then what?

38:09.310 --> 38:10.551
- [sighs]

38:12.896 --> 38:15.965
- This has been
one of those days, Carl,

38:15.965 --> 38:17.793
when I question
my children's commitment

